The Herald Herald Reporter The late Foreign Affairs and International Trade Minister, Dr Sibusiso Busi Moyo, has been declared a national hero. The message was delivered by Defence and War Veteran Affairs Minister Oppah Muchinguri-Kashiri who had been sent by President Mnangagwa to the Moyo family in Harare this evening. <img class="size-full wp-image-525740" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Screenshot-2021-01-21-at-19.29.01.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Screenshot-2021-01-21-at-19.29.01.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Screenshot-2021-01-21-at-19.29.01-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Defence and War Veteran Affairs Minister Oppah Muchinguri-Kashiri announces hero status of Foreign Affairs and International Trade Minister, Dr Sibusiso Busi Moyo to the family in Harare this evening Burial arrangements will be announced in due course. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-525741" src="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Screenshot-2021-01-21-at-19.28.13.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Screenshot-2021-01-21-at-19.28.13.jpg 680w, https://www.herald.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/01/Screenshot-2021-01-21-at-19.28.13-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Minister Moyo died of Covid-19-related complications yesterday. 